Feature: Migrate Venues Screen to SwiftUI

🧠 Overview

The system currently uses a UIKit-based `VenuesVC` that supports multiple operational modes:

- Standard venue browsing
- Admin venue selection
- Map-based venue selection

The screen relies on:

- Storyboard segues for navigation
- Global shared state (`PlacesData_`, `PlacesData2_`)
- NotificationCenter for cross-screen communication
- MapKit for location interaction

This feature introduces a SwiftUI-based implementation that:

- Preserves all existing behaviors
- Replaces imperative UI logic with declarative state
- Gradually removes global/shared state dependencies

🔁 Modes (Core Requirement)

1. Standard Mode
- Displays venues for selected movie
- Allows navigation to venue details
- Shows inline details panel

2. Admin Mode (`adminPage == true`)
- Displays all locations
- Allows selecting a venue
- Sends selection via NotificationCenter

Event:
newScreenVenueSelected

3. Map Mode (`mapViewPage == true`)
- Displays filtered locations (`PlacesData2_`)
- Allows selecting a venue
- Updates map with annotation
- Sends selection via NotificationCenter

Event:
screeningVenueSelected

🔗 Current Architecture Constraints

Global State:
- PlacesData_
- PlacesData2_

Used for:
- Data sharing across screens
- Map interaction

Event System:
Uses NotificationCenter for:
- Navigation triggers (navigateBack)
- Venue selection events

Map Integration:
Uses:
- MKMapView
- Annotations
- Region updates

🎯 Goals (UPDATED)

- Support all three modes in SwiftUI
- Replace global state with structured state (gradually)
- Preserve NotificationCenter behavior (initially)
- Integrate MapKit using SwiftUI-compatible APIs
- Maintain compatibility with UIKit entry points

❗ Functional Requirements

Modes:
System MUST support:
- Standard mode
- Admin mode
- Map mode

Entry Points for each mode MUST remain functional via storyboard segues:
- AdminVC → VenuesVC (admin mode)
- MapViewController → VenuesVC (map mode)
- MoviesVC → VenuesVC (standard mode)
- VenuesView → VenuesDetailsVC (details panel)

Design:
- System MUST display correct UI for each mode
- Venues list MUST be populated correctly based on mode
- Venue selection MUST trigger appropriate events based on mode
- Venue details MUST be shown in standard mode on selection
- Venues list MUST be scrollable and selectable in all modes
- Venues list MUST adhere list based design and styling
- Venues list MUST display venues pictures and names correctly
- Venues list shows the location details on selection in the bottom of the screen in standard mode
- Venues list has a button to navigate to the details screen in standard mode
- Venues list is not devided vertically, but horizontally, when in standard mode to show the details panel in the bottom

Feature flags:
- System MUST use `adminPage` to toggle admin mode
- System MUST use `mapViewPage` to toggle map mode

Map Behavior:
- System MUST display map when in map mode
- System MUST update annotation on selection
- System MUST center map on selected location

Event Handling:
System MUST:
- Listen to existing notifications
- Emit same notifications as UIKit version

Global Data:
- System MUST initially support existing global arrays
- System SHOULD allow future migration away from globals

📊 Success Criteria

- All three modes behave identically to UIKit version
- Map interaction works correctly
- NotificationCenter events still fire
- No regression in admin/map workflows
